blocks.name: rencldnfi
blocks.content: A set of real numbers which comes arbitrarily close to some target yet excludes it is infinite. The work is done in ~ rencldnfilem using infima; this theorem removes the requirement that A be nonempty. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 19-Oct-2014.)
